The paper discusses the interaction between humans and machines in various contexts such as emergency decision support, healthcare, and smart homes. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the capabilities and impact of machine actors, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also touches upon trust implications in human-machine networks, which could be relevant to the Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of machine agency on networks, which could be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
